&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;&lt;a href=&#34;https://pricejh.com/readingplan/&#34;&gt;ReadingPlan&lt;/a&gt; helps you track your progress as you read through the Bible. You can start a plan at any time, progressing at your own rate or on the schedule dictated by the plan. You can optionally link to an online bible site to see the plan&amp;rsquo;s readings in the application&amp;rsquo;s built-in web view, or open the reading in one of many native bible apps.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From 2016 to 2020, we had a church app. It had sermons, events, and our Bible reading plan. However, the app never got traction and the company behind it phased out support for the app platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Further, after reading &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.nucleus.church/blog/church-app/&#34;&gt;this article&lt;/a&gt;, I thought it best to sunset the app.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, I still missed the ability to track Bible reading.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://pricejh.com/readingplan/&#34;&gt;ReadingPlan&lt;/a&gt; does a great job of filling that niche as it allows churches and organizations to upload their own plans by emailing the plan (uniquely formatted) to the app creator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the &lt;a href=&#34;https://pricejh.com/readingplan/&#34;&gt;ReadingPlan&lt;/a&gt; app itself, the ReadingPlan website hosts &lt;a href=&#34;https://pricejh.com/readingplan/cplans/all_plans.html&#34;&gt;numerous plans&lt;/a&gt; which can be added to the app or just browsed to get ideas and inspiration for your own Bible reading plan.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There seem to be five basic Bible reading plans:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/tags/through&#34;&gt;Through&lt;/a&gt; the Bible – Classic and straightforward, but not without &lt;a href=&#34;/thoughts/through&#34;&gt;challenges&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/plans/daily-office&#34;&gt;Daily office lectionary&lt;/a&gt; – Based on, for example, The Book of Common Prayer (2019) of the Anglican Church in North America (ACNA). (&lt;a href=&#34;https://northamanglican.com/a-new-daily-office-lectionary/&#34;&gt;Fascinating article&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://anglicancompass.com/category/anglicanism/daily-office-prayer/&#34;&gt;resources&lt;/a&gt; on the ACNA 2019 Daily Office.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thematic – Such as &lt;a href=&#34;https://my.bible.com/reading-plans&#34;&gt;those found at Bible.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Customized – Like &lt;a href=&#34;https://bibleplan.org/plans/prof-horner/&#34;&gt;Professor Horner&amp;rsquo;s plan&lt;/a&gt; which has 10 chapters per day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DIY – Using a generic Bible &lt;a href=&#34;https://visualunit.me/2010/12/14/bible-reading-chart/&#34;&gt;chart&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://bit.ly/3V4uAIu&#34;&gt;check sheet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://biblicalspirituality.org/article/bible-reading/&#34;&gt;record&lt;/a&gt;, or app like BibleTracker (&lt;a href=&#34;https://apps.apple.com/us/app/my-bible-tracker/id1530078172&#34;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://bit.ly/3UA5Sz9&#34;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;), Bible Reading Assistant (&lt;a href=&#34;https://apps.apple.com/us/app/bible-reading-assistant/id1473756195&#34;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://bit.ly/3FxMfUr&#34;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;), Tracks – Bible Companion (&lt;a href=&#34;https://apps.apple.com/us/app/tracks-bible-companion/id1231878723&#34;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://bit.ly/3VZibpN&#34;&gt;Android&lt;/a&gt;), or Daily Soul Bread (&lt;a href=&#34;https://apps.apple.com/us/app/daily-soul-bread/id1175130611&#34;&gt;iOS&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

